title: monospaced - york
content:
I cannot find this font. can anyone help?

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20090903141326im_/http:/typophile.com/files/yyy_6720.jpg)
author: vector

comments.content: Whatever it is, it’s not monospaced.
Sorry, it reminded me of a monospaced/typewriter font like courier. Any close suggestions?

<cite>WTF fails once again.</cite>

Yes, of course, but since vector was asking suggestions…

The serifs on this are unbracketed slabs, for the most part. I have not been able to find an exact match, and I wonder if you have other letters including caps that you can show us?

So far one of the closest I found was Ray Larabie’s [Marion](http://web.archive.org/web/20090903141326/http:/new.myfonts.com/fonts/typodermic/marion/regular/characters.html).

- Mike Yanega
